caption: My favorite go to is the Upside Down. If you like tequila please get this! We shared a charcuterie board, which had a ton of cheeses and meats. As always downtown can be pricy, but I feel like you really get what you pay for here - food quality! Highly recommend this place to anyone. Amazing!!!
Clean place, friendly staff, generally good"!!
Outdoor seating, service is adequate, menu is sandwiches/salads.
Truly a hidden gem and by far my favorite spot to unwind and have a delicious old fashioned.
The burger and the soups are fantastic
Incredible whisky selection

Had a 🍺 here after work last night.  Decent beers on tap.  Happened to had just blown the keg of the hazy IPA I ordered but managed to find another IPA that suited just fine.  Service was quick.  We had a work happy hour here before and ordered apps that were pretty decent too.  Nice little watering hole.  👍🏻👍🏻
Great food, drinks and people :-)
Last Text Drink was great!  Good hummus.
The atmosphere is nice and the service is good, But unlike Asadito and Wak n' Bao, the food here isn't.
Great whiskey/bourbon/scotch selection (Wednesday is half price whiskeys!).  Food was different but very good.  The waitress we had was amazing. 10/10 will be back again

The food wasn't bad, but nothing to race about either. Where the three stars comes from is the service. Our waitress was less than welcoming and seemed more annoyed with us than anything.  Considering the higher price point and nice decor, we expected a bit more from Slightly Toasted.  Maybe if we had a different server, things would be different, but our first impression wasn't good.
Great atmosphere, huge whiskey selection.
Delicious food, and a great selection of beers. The atmosphere is pretty laid back, and everyone that works there seems very nice.
Fairly solid old fashions!
Decent cafe
Limited breakfast menu. The avocado toast was really good and the portion size was filling. Liked the ambience.

Great neighborhood bar. They have a great beer selection, always have barrel aged beers on tap. The food is great as well. Service is fast and friendly. Would recommend this bar to anyone who's in the area. Do try their mushroom and quinoa burger and the burrata salad.
Great whiskey selection, knowledgeable staff, great monthly whiskey events
Good. I recommend. Nice summer out in Chicago
Great coffee, delicious quick bite and long discussion.
Awesome! Wish I wasn't working so I could get. The name.
Great downtown spot for lunch or after work. Didn't get to dive into the whiskey this time,  but will do next time
Food sucked
Great bar with lots of whiskey and fun owners
Vast selection of bourbon and scotch ..veryfresh vegtables.
Great rye selection!
Awesome whiskey selection

Underwhelming. Used to have a beef tartare toast that was amazing. Now, it's bacon and cheese. Given demand and possibly risk, I understand and didn't wanna knock em for it. I tried the avocado toast now. Given that it's 9 (vs 7), and has no bacon, cheese or egg, I was expecting something amazing. Well, the taste was definitely arranged well.....but I got maybe a quarter avocado, at most. Wow.
Great coffee and wonderful service

I came to Slightly Toasted for lunch and I found my new favorite. Aly helped me with the menu in recommending the different menu items good for sharing. First from the "Shareables", we ordered the Garlic Pretzel Knot and I've never had anything like this. It was very flavorful. The mustard really put it all together, and the buratta on top.... It was perfect. Then we decided to order a burger to split, so we ordered the ST Burger, it was very good. Definitely would come here again for the burger. We also ordered the Avocado toast, my favorite. It was very fresh and a good amount of flavor. Truly appreciated that. Also, the  bacon and egg toast was really good. The sourdough bread with both of the toast was perfect. Just the toast alone, is a great reason to come here for breakfast, lunch, or even dinner. Definitely adding this to my favorites list. PERIODT!
Great first time 👌🏼Food was on point. Service was even better. Thanks Aly!

Really an excellent beer selection and very dedicated and impressive whiskey selection. The food was good as well. There's almost always something on special too. Highly recommended for a quick stop or a long night, especially if proximity to Ogilvie is important.
That banh mi sandwich was a really nice surprise. Good food - still need to visit for happy hour; haven't done that yet.
Accommodated our big party on short notice. Half price booze on Wednesday. What's not to like?
Great selection, bit expensive
Great looking staff.... I think a few of them are in magazines.

One of the best selections of bourbon in the area.  I've had lots of Manhattans, but this place made an outstanding one. The food menu is small but a little something for everyone. The service was excellent.   If you haven't tried this place you should.
Great place, especially if you're trying to unwind from work.
Good food, drinks, and vibes! Service is a bit slow but great after work spot.
Great food. Excellent beer and whiskey selections.

Love this place. The menu seems small and kind of underwhelming but just give it a chance. The quality of the food and flavor is killer. To top it off the beer list always features some newer local brew and happy hour drink specials are a thing. Space is comfortable and clean - not sure what's up with the comment about dirty fingernails.

Good if limited menu, but the waiters have had dirty (and I mean a line of black under each nail) fingernails every time I've been in. I know they're not cooking the food and shouldn't be touching it between kitchen and table, but I'm not sold on a restaurant that doesn't prioritize visible cleanliness.
Food was good..
Nice spot for a quick bite and drinks.
great spot for a good lunch time old fashion. the food is good too.
Great place to work during the work week. Good food, great coffee, and cocktails for those certain days you need an extra kick
Bar tenders we're not as prompt as other places in the same area
Really excellent food.  Priced accordingly, unfortunately.  Absolutely worth it though!
Great spot for food, to work or just coffee. Lots of seating available and great vibe. Service was spot on as well.
I had the saddest pork belly of my life at this restaurant. It was tiny, completely cold, horribly chewy, tasteless, and $14 to boot. Also the service wasn't very good.
Great whiskey selection and good cocktails
Nice place close to union Statiin. Good choice od Bourbon, scotch & whiskies. Trendy had appitisers, with a group from work.
It's pretty good but the portion of food could be a bit bigger
Like the ambiance here
Terrible food but lots of whiskey
bad service
Went with a group and had reservations. Can get very loud.
Great toast, great whisky. More?
I've been for coffee+pastries and drinks+dinner, and all were good. Looking forward to making this a regular go-to spot.
The ambiance is excellent, as is the food, coffee and service.  We were tempted to stick around for cocktails, but it was still breakfast. We'll definitely return if we are in Chicago again.
Diverse beer selection. Solid cocktails. Gourmet coffee and espresso. Friendly service. This place has it all.
Food was good but a bit skimpy in size. Service was excellent. It was very loud
Very good food. Love the sandwiches and chips. Crushed ice is always a plus. Would have loved to get a cocktail here as well.
Some of the cocktails were good, especially the one with an orange flavored ice
Good for work lunch. I got the chicken pesto sandwich which was great! Cozy ambience and very good service!
Great sandwiches

The turkey sandwich is a ridiculous waste of $12.  Small amount of cheap deli meat, two small slices from a roma-style tomato and a meager smear of guacamole.  Save a couple bucks and get Potbelly across the street.  I won't rule out they crush drinks...didn't have any and other reviews make it sound very promising.  But bail on the food, at least the turkey sandwich.

What a GREAT place tucked away in the 540 building.... great selection of whiskey and more importantly, an incredibly knowledgeable staff who is full of recommendations and back stories to each selection.

In an area full of depressing train bars and whatever it is you call Dylan's, this bar stands out as a classy choice, with high quality drinks and tasty food. If you're looking for somewhere to go after work that isn't filled with a bunch of sad people downing well martinis before they get on a train to see their families in the suburbs, this is the place.  That said, it's my experience with the staff that has me giving three stars. I always get the feeling I'm annoying the servers by wanting to order. And that's after a long wait just to find one.  In my experience, this isn't a place that will make you feel particularly welcome. But, again, the drinks and food are top notch, so if you don't particularly care about the (lack of) love, I highly recommend Slightly Toasted.
I love this place

I have been to Slightly Toasted a couple dozen times just because they are located in the same building that I work in. The service is always on the slower side and often on the VERY slow side. They also charge a dollar more if you want a larger ice cube in your old-fashioned (or whatever cocktail you prefer) which is pretty annoying and the drink is expensive enough to begin with. Speed up service and show a little enthusiasm and you'd have 4-5 stars since your drinks are good once you finally get served.

Disclaimer: I know the owners. Ever since this place opened, it's been the best. The coffee is spectacular, the food is magnificent, and the staff is superb! Would highly recommend at any hour they are open!
This place is awesome. Everything tasted great and prices are pretty reasonable. I think the best part is the atmosphere. It's just a really nice space to spend a couple hours.
Great mixed drinks with a good atmosphere to talk and hang out.
Great food the coffee was wonderful and the guy before the bar was very personable

If you love whiskey, bourbon, and scotch, you've gotta check this place out. They have a great deal on Mondays and the staff didn't even balk at my request for a separate glass of ice (so I can control how much- or little- goes into my drink). The atmosphere is sophisticated but relaxed, and it's a perfect place to unwind after a stressful work day.

I sampled a few of the whisky's off their impressive menu.  The selection was impressive.  The service was great.  The atmosphere is also really nice.  Although the place was crowded, it was terribly loud.  O, and the prices were great as well.  Great Chicago spot.
Great bar!!
Good place to Chill.

Friendly staff, but I didn't take kindly to their method of neglecting our table and then bringing the check as the next stop when we all (6 of us) ended up ordering another round or two. Otherwise great place with great drinks!

The toasts were delicious. I shared 2 savory and 1 sweet toast with my boyfriend. It was just enough for us. The plates are small but packed with flavors that woke up my sleepy taste buds. Huge fan of the bourbon nutella toast. You also get free refills on the groundswell roasters coffee.
The food is ok if you need a quick bite to eat  most of it is pretty basic
Great whiskey selection!

Service was friendly and prompt and when they made a mistake on our order, they fixed it on their own and comped our drink. Cocktails and toast tasted great. Pleasant causal ambiance. Good for after work drinks.
Great place to have coffee near 🔥
Cool place to toast
As advertised, the whisky selection was excellent! Half-price Mondays made it that much better! The food was tasty too - not sure how healthy though.

I'm being generous with three stars only because the wine was decent.  My friend and I had lunch here several weeks prio and really liked the ambiance and salads.  Very fresh.  We enjoyed it so much we decided to go again for drinks and appetizers.  We enjoyed our wine but we were very disappointed in the Chef's choice- meat & cheese board.  They should have told us they were out of that item because what we ended up with was crumbled blue cheese and crumbled feta cheese,  something you would expect on a salad.  The other cheese on the board was sliced cheese,  something you would expect on a burger.  The real disappointment was what they considered prosciutto,  which in reality was bacon.  Really, bacon on a meat & cheese board?  We may go back but not for the bacon & processed cheese board!

The food was really good and also the coffee, the service was also good, however they need to pay attention on details. I tried to charge my cellphone in the bar and they went crazy because I was not sitting in the bar section, they make me unplugged my cell.
Nice spot to stop for a morning cup of coffee. The place is nice and quiet. The decor is beautiful. And the coffee is delicous. I just got regular coffee but they have specialty drinks as well.
Well named cocktails.
Awesome selection of whiskey with knowledgable staff and delicious food!
Very good. Servers know their whiskey.

Don't let the main focus of the menu deter you from stopping here. Ive been here several times: All menu items, including the toast, are surprisingly well prepared and taste great. If that's not for you, they also have regular sandwich and salad options.  The main draw for me, in addition to the location, is the extensive whiskey menu. If you dine/drink inside, there is also a Nintendo 64 w some key games.  Enjoy

A bit pricey. If it wasn't theday they have half price bourbon, it would have been really high. Service was adequate. The place wasn't bad just not good enough to make me want to come back. If I were with a group, and they wanted to go there, I wouldn't put up a fuss.
It is great the burger is fantastic
Great atmosphere. Great drinks!
Nice place in the west loop. Huge whiskey selection and they habe really good toast.

Great selection of local beers, whiskeys and delicious food. Gets very busy and service times can be a little long, but staff are helpful and friendly. Great cocktails, and a fun random-drink game you can win a pour of a really nice whiskey too.
Average lunch spot downtown.  Outdoor seating, service is adequate, menu is sandwiches/salads.
Food fine. Beers on smaller side. Forgot the happy hour on our check. Was ok.
Excellent rotating craft beer selection and plenty of whiskey (if that's your thing).  I've tried everything on their menu and it's all solid.  You really can't go wrong with their toasts though.
Is ok bar is still a little rough around the edges and still finding their way

Such a great spot close to the Metra. There is an outdoor seating option and large group tables. Good cocktails, and appetizers. Wait staff is really friendly and if they don't know the answer to your questions they will definitely find out.

I've been here several times, both with friends & coworkers. The atmosphere is pretty decent for an office bar. The fireplace is a nice touch & I've never had a bad service experience here. The draft menu is one of the better ones for the neighborhood, but prices are a little high. Same thing with the whiskey list. The food has always been good! I'm particularly a fan of the strawberries & cream /ricotta toast.
Great lunch and good atmosphere.  A very good selection of beer.
Delicious food, coffee and drinks
Took over an hour to get served here.
Cool environment with great drinks and even better snacks. The staff was also very attentive and efficient.

This is a nice, more laid back bar in the West loop. Staff is nice, but really weird and sit of disorganized. The beer selection is minimal, but had something do for most tastes. I'm not Nick into bad, so i didn't do a toast flight, but i saw some people with a nice charcuterie plate that i would try next time. They have an okay happy hour 6-9.

Great great place! First, I loved the idea of the concept of toasts, and on top of that, the toasts were very good - awesome quality - it was delicious! They have a very long lists of whiskies - scotch - bourbons which my husband loved. The wine list is smaller though, but I was not disapointed with the 2 wines I took which I usually am in other bars... We were very surprised of the quality of what this place serves, drinks and food are very good, it is a great place to relax. I recommend going with the toasts rather than the starters, it seemed to me that the toast were bigger portions than the starters.
Their 4 dollar toasts are the best deal in the loop.  Immense whiskey selection and a wonderful staff.
Drinks are great
Had the hummus toast and an americano. Was blown away by the flavor and quality. The prices are great too. I'll definitely come back.
